    "12 In short, liability causes the prices of products to reflect their risks (Polinsky & Shavell, 2010, 1440).",
    "Both strict liability and negligence induce producers to choose the optimal precautions when consumers are perfectly informed about care and perceive risks accurately (Friehe et al., 2022, 55).",
